  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mainstreaming Social Accountability in Mongolia (MASAM)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall goal of the program is to contribute to citizens in poor localities having increased access to public decision-making processes and quality services through social accountability.
 The program objective is to mainstream social accountability for more transparent, accountable and effective public resource management at national and local levels by (1) increasing the capacity of CSOs to hold government to account; and (2) strengthening the institutionalization of social accountability by improving the effectiveness, formalization and sustainability of disclosure and participation mechanisms. Through social accountability, citizens in poor localities will have increased access to public decision-making processes and quality services.
 The program will work with civil society organizations, especially national networks of CSOs, and with relevant government agencies. Targeting networks of CSOs and government agencies will ensure that policies, mechanisms, and lessons are implemented and disseminated nationwide. This will contribute to scaling up social accountability in Mongolia and enhance the sustainability of the interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
